---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer vs Webflow: Which Should You Choose? (2025)',
  description: 'Framer vs Webflow comparison. Framer is newer, faster, easier. Webflow is mature, powerful, steeper learning curve. Which is right for your website?',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer vs Webflow', 'Framer or Webflow', 'no-code website builder', 'visual website builder', 'Framer comparison'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builders · Honest Comparison
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer vs Webflow
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Both are visual website builders. Framer is newer, faster to learn, optimized for marketing sites. Webflow is more mature, more powerful, steeper learning curve. Which to choose depends on your use case and learning patience.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick verdict: Choose Framer if you want to build quickly and easily. Choose Webflow if you need maximum control and don't mind learning. Framer wins on speed and ease. Webflow wins on power and flexibility. Both are excellent - wrong choice is annoying but fixable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          I use both daily. Framer for rapid prototypes and marketing sites. Webflow for complex client projects and custom functionality. They're not mutually exclusive - you can use both for different projects.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      At a Glance
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Webflow</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Learning curve</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Easy-medium</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Medium-hard</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Starting price</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Free, then $16/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$23/mo</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Marketing sites, portfolios</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Complex sites, client work</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Design approach</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Free-form canvas</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Box-model based</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">CMS</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Basic</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Advanced</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Maturity</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Newer (2020)</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Mature (2013)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framer Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Framer: Newer, Faster, Easier
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">What Framer Does Well</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>✓ <strong>Fast learning curve:</strong> Up and running in days, not weeks</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Rapid development:</strong> Build sites 2-3x faster than Webflow</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Figma-like interface:</strong> Familiar if you use design tools</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>AI features:</strong> AI site generation, AI copywriting</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Great templates:</strong> Modern, design-focused templates</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Responsive by default:</strong> Easy mobile adaptation</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>CMS included:</strong> Good enough for most content sites</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Free tier:</strong> Actually usable for testing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Framer Limitations</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>✗ <strong>Newer platform:</strong> Fewer resources, smaller community</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Less powerful CMS:</strong> Not for complex content sites</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Limited export:</strong> Can't export clean code like Webflow</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Fewer advanced features:</strong> Webflow has more bells and whistles</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>E-commerce limited:</strong> Not for serious online stores</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Some bugs:</strong> Newer platform = more edge cases</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Framer Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Mini:</strong> Free (great for testing, limited)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Basic:</strong> $16/month ($192/year) - Remove branding, custom domain</li>
          <li>• <strong>Pro:</strong> $25/month ($300/year) - CMS, 5 sites</li>
          <li>• <strong>Dynamic:</strong> From $223/month for complex sites</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">Framer is slightly cheaper than Webflow for comparable plans. Annual billing saves ~20%.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Webflow Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Webflow: Mature, Powerful, Steeper Learning Curve
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">What Webflow Does Well</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>✓ <strong>Proven mature:</strong> 10+ years of development, very stable</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Powerful CMS:</strong> Best-in-class content management</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Clean code export:</strong> Can export HTML/CSS/JS</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Advanced interactions:</strong> Powerful animation system</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Huge community:</strong> Endless tutorials, templates, resources</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Client-ready:</strong> Standard for agency work</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>More features:</strong> E-commerce, memberships, logic</li>
          <li>✓ <strong>Granular control:</strong> Design precision down to pixels</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Webflow Limitations</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>✗ <strong>Steep learning curve:</strong> Takes weeks to get proficient</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Slower development:</strong> More methodical, less rapid</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Expensive:</strong> $23+/month, adds up quickly</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Platform lock-in:</strong> Can't export easily (despite export feature)</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>E-commerce limited:</strong> Not for large stores (use Shopify)</li>
          <li>✗ <strong>Overkill for simple sites:</strong> Powerful but complex</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Webflow Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Starter:</strong> $18/month ($216/year) - 2 sites, Webflow branding</li>
          <li>• <strong>Basic:</strong> $23/month ($276/year) - 2 sites, no branding</li>
          <li>• <strong>CMS:</strong> $39/month ($468/year) - 3 sites, advanced CMS</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business:</strong> $87/month ($1,044/year) - 10 sites, team features</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">Webflow is slightly more expensive than Framer. Annual billing saves ~20%. Hosting, SSL, backups included.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Differences -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Key Differences Explained
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Learning Curve</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Days to weeks to get productive. Feels like design tools you already know. Drag, drop, resize. Intuitive. Most people are building real sites within first week.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Weeks to months to get proficient. Feels different from design tools. Concepts like classes, flexbox, grid take time. Most people need 2-3 months before feeling confident.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Winner:</strong> Framer for ease. Webflow requires more patience.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Development Speed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> 2-3x faster than Webflow. Less setup, faster styling, instant preview. Great for rapid prototyping, marketing sites, MVPs.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> More methodical. Slower but more precise. Better for complex sites where speed isn't only priority. Faster overall once proficient, but slower initially.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Winner:</strong> Framer for speed. Webflow for precision.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">CMS Capabilities</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Good CMS for basic content sites. Blogs, portfolios, simple collections work well. Not for complex multi-level content or advanced filtering.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Industry-leading CMS. Can build complex content architectures, advanced filtering, multi-collections. Power user features make CMS incredibly flexible.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Winner:</strong> Webflow for complex CMS. Framer for basic CMS.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Code Quality</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Generates clean code using React. Modern, performant. Good for SEO. Code is decent but optimized more for Framer's system than general use.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Generates semantic HTML/CSS. Very clean, very organized. Widely considered best-in-class for generated code. Can export and use elsewhere (with limitations).</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Winner:</strong> Webflow for cleanest code. Framer is good but Webflow is better.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Community and Resources</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer:</strong> Smaller but growing community. Fewer templates, fewer tutorials, fewer third-party resources. Newer platform = less ecosystem.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Massive community. Thousands of templates, endless tutorials, active forums, third-party tools, agencies everywhere. If you're stuck, someone has solved it.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Winner:</strong> Webflow by a mile. Ecosystem is huge advantage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Best Use Cases</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4"><strong>Framer excels at:</strong> Marketing sites, landing pages, portfolios, rapid prototypes, MVPs. Sites where speed and ease matter more than complex features.</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow excels at:</strong> Client work, complex sites, advanced CMS, custom functionality, agency output. Sites where power and flexibility matter more than speed.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Winner:</strong> Tie - different tools for different jobs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Who Should Choose What?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Framer If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>✓ You want to build fast (speed is priority)</li>
          <li>✓ You're building marketing sites or portfolios</li>
          <li>✓ You're a beginner (easier learning curve)</li>
          <li>✓ You like Figma/design tools (familiar interface)</li>
          <li>✓ Budget is tight (slightly cheaper)</li>
          <li>✓ You need AI features (site generation, copywriting)</li>
          <li>✓ Rapid prototyping matters to you</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Webflow If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>✓ You're doing client work (industry standard)</li>
          <li>✓ You need complex CMS features</li>
          <li>✓ You want cleanest code output</li>
          <li>✓ You value community resources and templates</li>
          <li>✓ You need advanced interactions</li>
          <li>✓ You're building complex sites</li>
          <li>✓ You have time to learn (not in rush)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final Verdict -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Final Verdict</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">I use both. Here's my honest take:</p>

      <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="font-bold mb-2">I choose Framer for:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Marketing landing pages</li>
            <li>• Personal portfolios</li>
            <li>• Rapid client prototypes</li>
            <li>• MVPs and test sites</li>
            <li>• "I need this done by tomorrow" projects</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="font-bold mb-2">I choose Webflow for:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Client projects (professionally expected)</li>
            <li>• Complex sites with advanced features</li>
            <li>• Blogs with heavy CMS requirements</li>
            <li>• Sites I know will need ongoing maintenance</li>
            <li>• Projects where code quality matters most</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">The "wrong" choice isn't fatal. Both can build great sites. Framer gets you there faster. Webflow gets you there with more control. Neither is bad choice.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">My recommendation: Start with Framer. If you outgrow it, switch to Webflow. Easier to start simple and upgrade than to start complex and give up. Framer's lower learning curve means you'll actually finish projects. Webflow's complexity means some people abandon sites halfway.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Both are excellent. Wrong choice is annoying, not disastrous. Right choice depends on your use case, patience, and timeline. Pick one, start building, learn as you go.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-ai-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer AI Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full Framer review</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full Webflow review</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/ai-website-builders-compared" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">AI Website Builders Compared</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full comparison guide</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Different approaches compared</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
